    'Spiral Turn:\nPut full weight on the spiral foot (in this case, RF), with head, center, hips all stacked up. Do not leave hip behind. Put whole weight on foot as fast as possible before doing spiral.\nTurning, Man lead arm, move elbow across body, do not turn and leave arm and elbow behind.\nAs spiraling, keep thighs crossed, helps to pull legs together fast.\nUndertuned spiral - an alternative:\nMan: turn 1/8 L over 7-10, dancing a fwd lock to end in Open Position.\nLady: \n3/4 L after placing step 5, to end in Tandem Position.\nStep 6: LF fwd\nStep 7: RF fwd in line with LF, then continue to turn 1/2 to end with RF back.\nStep 8-10: Back lock LRL.\nAlternative finishing positions\nOpen Position: Man turns 3/8 to L over steps 7-10.\nOpen CPP\nContact Position: ( Known as Closed Spiral)\nMan turn 5/8 to L over steps 7-10, dancing the chasse side and slightly fwd, overturning Lady, keeping fingers lightly in contact with Lady''s waist throughout as Lady turns within the circle of his R arm. On 6: lower arms to normal position. Man keeps his RH in contact with Lady''s back to indicate finishing in contact position\nLady makes a complete turn L over steps 6-10, dancing the chasse with LF behind RF as Cuban Cross.\nLeft Side Position\nMan: no turn over 7 to 10, leading Lady to overturn on 7, lowering L arm and taking it slightly fwd.\nLady: turn an additional 1/8 to L on 7, using a loosely crossed spiral action\nBoth dance a fwd lock on steps 8-10.'
