    'Slight sway to L on 2 and 3',
    1
),
(
    '272cfab7-8210-3179-b52c-f17dee54eba5',
    '4fb53c2c-ebfc-373d-82dd-fb6b4fc18789',
    'continue to rise on 2',
    2
),
(
    '39723f3b-ce67-3998-817a-bb1b00450da2',
    '766063c3-7e60-3ff4-8951-16540d3ac40a',
    'Slight body turn to L',
    1
),
(
    'e9807afc-2e58-3279-b18e-5f0faa5909a4',
    '766063c3-7e60-3ff4-8951-16540d3ac40a',
    'Up. Lower e/o 3',
    2
),
(
    '396e5418-dea5-32a0-885c-9eb044fa530f',
    '4c00442e-d3a7-3c71-a03a-3f5117ca54a7',
    'If preferred, could be LF fwd with foot flat.',
    1
),
(
    '1ddad4c0-96d2-376b-ab86-bf67f433b1bb',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'The step needs to feel more free. Lady does not bend straight back, there is rotation and head continues to extend go along body line.',
    1
),
(
    'f546404d-5877-3a66-bb41-5f04b3769b94',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Prep: bend/lower left knee, shoulder level off, rotate hips to left. Do not send stomach muscle forward, i.e. do not stick tummy up to Man at this time. connect center into hip joint, hip has to be able to move.',
    2
),
(
    '32929bd5-da0b-37d2-84df-8896b512d9f3',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Big step back after rotating hips (if step is too short, upper body weight will take over when doing contra check), also need bigger step to create more extension. CMBP (do not get into Man''s space).',
    3
);

INSERT INTO dance_figure_step_comment (id, dance_figure_step_id, comment_text, display_order)
VALUES
(
    '0d9fb8e7-3e83-3af9-a4a5-85edfbbdc7d4',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'RF point back first, RF toe turned in (for better balance), then on ball of feet, keep right heel up (solid, not heel moving down and then up), weight split. body rotate to left, but keep left side up to Man (though body is turning left and shaping). Don''t break neck.',
    4
),
(
    'd2558956-053d-3367-9811-9ef4b466866e',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Keep left toe down on floor, do not lift L toe. LF is pretty much flat on floor.',
    5
),
(
    'd87af600-7949-31ab-bc0e-52dcce3679f2',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Flex both knees, at this time, weight in the middle, not on back foot. Get there first, then give (R) hip and ribs to Man for extension, left leg can go more straight at this time, allowing for more extension, putting a bit more weight on RF, take the center back, but keep R heel up, R leg is bent, then extend upper body diagonally back. Extend R arm to Man.',
    6
),
(
    '36b3dc77-331a-386f-a7fb-240df08acba7',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Lift glute and center up to Man. (butt cheek up) and give whole R side to Man. Imagine stretching R side longer to give to Man more, effect is shaping and extending to left.',
    7
),
(
    '3f19fef2-c1ea-3973-9728-94698b9cc2ea',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Upper body has the look of rotating/shaping to left (but don''t rotate away from Man, upper body and hip to Man), head "finishes" the extension with breathing. (Don''t be afraid to extend head more. Go into Man''s R hand.)',
    8
),
(
    'b2c05ca8-78c0-3c77-b516-cc5e7c9ff9dd',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'The whole body is not one straight piece. There is torch in upper body - rotation and sway (do not just bend backward) and at tail end, stretch even more before recovering. The elasticity doesn''t stop.',
    9
),
(
    'f8432e0c-7bc3-3798-9bfb-58b3f9607a88',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Continuous extension and all the way to head. Upper body, not locked and still, but stay soft and flexible, go and fill the space Man created with his R hand.',
    10
),
(
    '50fbd0f2-b728-30aa-8010-d136dc62fcf1',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Don''t "sit", don''t just go "down" which feels heavy. Continuous shaping and then bounce up. Man start recovering after Lady finish extending head.',
    11
),
(
    'f0acbebf-1f21-34c0-8edf-3d378e89d8e0',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Arms belong to partner, never pull arms back. extend the arm to give space.',
    12
),
(
    'df3afa67-3ee5-358b-a2be-371459b88797',
    '2cafb1ab-a2d6-3adc-a1de-cf7398918d5a',
    'Frame: breathe, need to feel "free". Create elasticity feeling, continuous movement out and come back (no stopping and then rotate. movement is smooth and light.)',
    13
),
(
    '7de74eb4-cdb2-3b7b-aa40-ddc16a65acef',
    '88ad4c71-409b-3370-8db1-bb5d4b45ad73',
    'Make sure to stay very left (has tendency to shift to R, get into Man''s space). Keep big frame and give R side to Man, don''t fall to PP.',
    1
),
(
    'b6b5ef78-59fc-3fcd-8562-0be804f50351',
    '88ad4c71-409b-3370-8db1-bb5d4b45ad73',
    'At end, start articulating head turn',
    2
),
(
    '338e4c04-184f-37bd-8b77-718fbc9eb8ba',
    '94ce452d-2b24-31f7-8241-8c5f707994c4',
    'Articulate head.',
    1
),
(
    'd38edd53-2e41-35ed-94f6-4751d9e499ee',
    '94ce452d-2b24-31f7-8241-8c5f707994c4',
    'Make sure R side is to Man.',
    2
),
(
    'af10141e-d3cd-34f2-94d9-d45a8800dd5d',
    '94ce452d-2b24-31f7-8241-8c5f707994c4',
    'Prep for next step: Lower first and step big.',
    3
),
(
    'fb91e008-78e7-38ab-8e64-f60ebe0effc7',
    '4e8388f5-06d3-3737-a2ac-ccad9457c24a',
    'Important to do CBM. Give Lady the indication of left by lowering.',
    1
),
(
    'ce85ca41-2d42-33fc-917a-1c1867dc270e',
    '4e8388f5-06d3-3737-a2ac-ccad9457c24a',
    'Early rise is to lead Lady into closing her feet into a heel turn.',
    2
),
(
    '103a8ade-7e65-38eb-aee7-466ade51693b',
    'b2a84867-eab7-31a4-8da5-bae0c49718a5',
    'Wait until the lady''s feet are together before taking this step.',
    1
),
(
    'db46ac0e-8e2c-3233-b0d7-4830af0de052',
    'b2a84867-eab7-31a4-8da5-bae0c49718a5',
    'Push LF to take the RF step.',
    2
),
(
    'e086f7c8-7117-3dd3-b5ed-2b90091d2c90',
    'b2a84867-eab7-31a4-8da5-bae0c49718a5',
    'When taking step, point RF forward with straight knees, then step onto the straight knee and turn to L.',
    3
),
(
    '9c6b40b3-5308-3e04-8a9d-fe759cff0168',
    'b2a84867-eab7-31a4-8da5-bae0c49718a5',
    'Track your RF, don''t do ronde. It will help with balance.',
    4
),
(
    '0f63cc73-c76e-3400-9a0d-f28c055e0300',
    'b2a84867-eab7-31a4-8da5-bae0c49718a5',
    'Think about getting hips around, rather than shoulders or feet. Same for second step on any turn where Man is going forward.',
    5
),
(
    'd5ef824f-fce7-34ea-9a04-44ef316e76bd',
    'b2a84867-eab7-31a4-8da5-bae0c49718a5',
    'Lengthen spine, don''t bend forward.',
    6
),
(
    'dfd40986-e7ad-31ec-8ca3-bd2bd96aff7d',
    '3dd18162-f1bd-3961-8de7-40f4c5042950',
    'settle and then drive to next step. Keep lengthening the spine.',
    1
),
(
    '2e28b692-7b81-3f35-8a55-5441d0bef3b0',
    '1e89f915-7452-39c1-a8cc-76edef25a885',
    'Be active, Lady "takes over", swing forward. Bigger step, push off left foot, get around (or "through") partner with more power.',
    1
),
(
    'b21383ea-8d43-3191-b51f-f0a7cbeb0046',
    '1e89f915-7452-39c1-a8cc-76edef25a885',
    'RF forward should be crossing LOD, Man is at one place, do not peel off from him, keep hips distance (on the right side), don''t gap.',
    2
),
(
    '705db3e8-350e-3c2f-bdcb-4c20a1ab0c47',
    '1e89f915-7452-39c1-a8cc-76edef25a885',
    'Stay with Man, keep on his R side.',
    3
),
(
    '326a7dd6-fe7f-3ff3-9a88-932e141d6172',
    'c241da82-3d2a-3140-a178-a13ce5b85b79',
    'Very important to do CBM, with CBM shoulder will clear way for Man to pass. Keep shoulder flat, and do not drop it on one side, do not pull left shoulder away from Man (It will "feel" left shoulder is "up", but in fact it will be flat.)',
    1
),
(
    'da98d131-c12d-347f-bae0-9070c8aa4d12',
    'c241da82-3d2a-3140-a178-a13ce5b85b79',
    'Lift center, shoulder slightly to R, left side positive on left turning figures.',
    2
),
(
    '1273a016-79d8-322e-b7f8-ef27bdfa6ad0',
    'c241da82-3d2a-3140-a178-a13ce5b85b79',
    'Step directly back moving down the floor, turn RF in. Do not step to the side, bigger step.',
    3
),
(
    '8b1eebf2-d913-35cd-81b2-3833d4cd04b8',
    'c241da82-3d2a-3140-a178-a13ce5b85b79',
    'Start the turn with head (not including shoulder), using head weight. Keep the head going left and look over your shoulder the whole time to avoid being pulled into the center of the turn.',
    4
),
(
    '1e098e91-0589-337d-a7b8-90f9aee9f920',
    'c241da82-3d2a-3140-a178-a13ce5b85b79',
    'Stay very left to Man, give left side to Man more, do not get in front of Man.',
    5
),
(
    '7cd178aa-00b7-3bc7-bfe8-f5f1d7d6b483',
    'c241da82-3d2a-3140-a178-a13ce5b85b79',
    'Do not pull left shoulder away from Man, i.e. do not peel off left side. Head can stretch more to left, move center (suck tummy). right arm to Man (this is from extending back).',
    6
),
(
    '8c51ceb8-15c0-38a8-be55-bf6b20aee41a',
    'c241da82-3d2a-3140-a178-a13ce5b85b79',
    'Use Man, lower first, move center, and then stepping RF/ R leg back, get on to the leg. Don''t fall back or lean forward. Keep spine upright.',
    7
),
(
    'ef98e3e8-3eb4-3c28-a1e7-b5c95c169b7f',
    'c241da82-3d2a-3140-a178-a13ce5b85b79',
    'Show off extension during the whole spin figure by looking over the shoulder more.',
    8
),
(
    '0a3b7c31-711b-35d0-aa57-9ce494e5322f',
    '6a24e299-7043-309c-bf22-374ddf5aa176',
    'Don''t lift toes off ground (no need to show off the bottom of your shoe!), be sure feet are parallel and together.',
    1
),
(
    '90ff9ee6-3357-3848-bdf6-4cf99a9882e9',
    '6a24e299-7043-309c-bf22-374ddf5aa176',
    'Draw trailing foot in, close the foot slowly, both legs should straighten, do not rise too early (though Man is rising), rise after heel turned, weight transferred to LF.',
    2
),
(
    '0ea5666a-9d0f-30a0-b334-58daf857294c',
    '6a24e299-7043-309c-bf22-374ddf5aa176',
    'Use the rules of head movement, head turns first, slightly more to left (don''t do it too early, though). Keep head left to follow left elbow, and look over left shoulder the whole time to avoid being pulled into the center of the turn.',
    3
),
(
    '8e026588-07c1-3006-857d-cc2537439139',
    '6a24e299-7043-309c-bf22-374ddf5aa176',
    'Keep body contact with Man throughout the heel turn.',
    4
),
(
    'de31d2ae-2b15-3322-bac9-68c72bb16702',
    '6a24e299-7043-309c-bf22-374ddf5aa176',
    'Do not allow spine to straighten up, keep left.',
    5
),
(
    '189b85a4-6920-3edf-91bf-9665c737bab6',
    '6a24e299-7043-309c-bf22-374ddf5aa176',
    'Do not pause the turning action between 1 and 2, shoulder and head continue to turn left (while feet are together), then body follows in step 3 on ''&''.',
    6
),
(
    '56027338-7221-3e2d-ab36-6c6695e31f65',
    '6a24e299-7043-309c-bf22-374ddf5aa176',
    'Movement is continuous, but speed is different. "&3" is faster.',
    7
),
(
    'af334fee-d6a9-35d1-8ec3-329ef7ef3449',
    '00c3fc33-c33b-36d0-ae2c-76472fcdf8d4',
    'Be active, Lady "takes over", swing forward. Bigger step, push off left foot, get around (or "through") partner with more power.',
    1
),
(
    'ce81f506-d837-34f0-b2c3-4566305fedb4',
    '00c3fc33-c33b-36d0-ae2c-76472fcdf8d4',
    'RF forward should be crossing LOD, Man is at one place, do not peel off from him, keep hips distance (on the right side), don''t gap.',
    2
),
(
    'ccd90b35-f359-369f-a02f-432f77875581',
    '00c3fc33-c33b-36d0-ae2c-76472fcdf8d4',
    'Stay with Man, keep on his R side.',
    3
),
(
    '6e01fbee-8b84-32ca-ab66-0cb13f4b9ea7',
    '1e75235a-2ac9-3ed5-a8f5-2c315c656352',
    'Cross feet (LF maintains pressure on ground while dragging to cross RF), lower into plie. Hips up the Man.',
    1
),
(
    '3cbf9e76-8b62-34fe-ace5-9be5a24c8660',
    '1e75235a-2ac9-3ed5-a8f5-2c315c656352',
    'Do not lower too early, lower on "&"',
    2
),
(
    '6ec96c6c-451e-3599-bc2f-3c2bfcc4bda4',
    '1e75235a-2ac9-3ed5-a8f5-2c315c656352',
    'Note: The Double Reverse Spin may be started DC, DW, or LOD. The amount of turn may vary between 3/4 and a whole turn.',
    3
),
(
    '5a5fb80b-4f1e-3a8f-acfb-039190e6aee6',
    '2a59d7d8-2912-3c47-9ac9-270e653e5d8c',
    'Start to turn L',
    1
),
(
    '2eaec094-1712-3618-b830-af7803c76471',
    'b8a58cc2-7e05-379b-b9f2-7a1aa12779c1',
    'R side leading',
    1
),
(
    'af9c0919-1f7d-386b-8147-6bcb82bdaf87',
    'b8a58cc2-7e05-379b-b9f2-7a1aa12779c1',
    'Moving down LOD',
    2
),
(
    '5e305f4d-0d32-383b-802d-1e79ff18fb6c',
    '1b973cb5-ed79-315a-89ac-30e90bf0aa0b',
    'body turns less',
    1
),
(
    'cdc3b8af-640c-3732-82b3-d32db0e0fecd',
    '3782fc8a-9bc8-3e67-8f5e-4a9d0af4a21e',
    'Similar to Double Reverse Spin, keep head left the whole time to help with the turn',
    1
),
(
    '91aedfcc-d519-39ca-9c9b-4720873014b1',
    '3782fc8a-9bc8-3e67-8f5e-4a9d0af4a21e',
    'Legs move backward, but body should not feel dancing backward',
    2
),
(
    '302b65c0-d854-34bb-b13a-09d18d05311a',
    '3782fc8a-9bc8-3e67-8f5e-4a9d0af4a21e',
    'body feels upward, leftward curve dancing into Man''s R side',
    3
),
(
    'e4a265a8-9df6-39ba-aa5f-e397e95d17f8',
    '3782fc8a-9bc8-3e67-8f5e-4a9d0af4a21e',
    'Lower first. RF back, curve, toe turned in. Center can''t fall back. Hips more forward and up to Man. Stay connected. Head goes even more left, stay outside',
    4
),
(
    'e6b4f7fe-33ee-3c8f-aa45-4f4509ed9877',
    '3782fc8a-9bc8-3e67-8f5e-4a9d0af4a21e',
    'Lower center rotates, upper center ("dial") sway only. shoulder does not fall back.',
    5
),
(
    '8420dba8-0c91-3e97-b956-2b87d37f8eb9',
    'b42f2778-be8c-3f5a-a562-decbfc533a55',
    'LF bigger step to match the first step, don''t cut it short',
    1
),
(
    '64fa6084-8d2f-3bda-bc64-27511ddb0a04',
    'b42f2778-be8c-3f5a-a562-decbfc533a55',
    'Curve',
    2
),
(
    '2376f859-8e35-32b3-9b5c-12054183955e',
    'b42f2778-be8c-3f5a-a562-decbfc533a55',
    ' moving BDC',
    3
),
(
    '100c43ad-6ba7-372d-a119-9e695c147ff7',
    'b42f2778-be8c-3f5a-a562-decbfc533a55',
    ' Suck tummy in, a little lift',
    4
),
(
    'afb00ed5-944d-3531-90b7-9b17c62f970a',
    'b42f2778-be8c-3f5a-a562-decbfc533a55',
    ' Stay connected with Man.',
    5
),
(
    '0b558a35-2329-3a28-b2a5-26b15d89be0f',
    'a4e7d67c-1bcf-3ba0-a31c-02d6123d11a7',
    'It feels hip is more twisted to left. Do not close left hip. Pick up left side and open left hip, Man''s right hip in middle of Lady''s left hip and center',
    1
),
(
    'd31bc48c-8dd1-3015-857a-d3da8d21e3e5',
    'a4e7d67c-1bcf-3ba0-a31c-02d6123d11a7',
    'Lady keeps center lifted to Man. Use tummy muscle, pull center.',
    2
),
(
    '782e3d40-4b96-3d2d-8eb1-d01ae8d511eb',
    '5fb90f12-9102-3bbc-98f0-386bb5ae3d2e',
    'Big step.',
    1
),
(
    'f354623c-7915-3559-87de-ca0835a8bafa',
    '697c46fd-17a2-354d-ba36-f3fd7ec2a728',
    'Swing forward. Whole R side to Man, stretch, To create big shape, breathe the frame. After stepping RF forward, turning body from bottom to up, feet, hip, upper toros, and lastly head (articulate head). Really delay head, slow. Feels like head isn''t finishing till way into next step.',
    1
),
(
    '5b6a2ca8-6832-32e5-a5d3-afbb9e9b6d55',
    '0041e7dd-3869-32a6-ba1b-b14911383beb',
    'Articulate LF coming out. soft knees, prepare next step by controlled lowering of knees',
    1
),
(
    '6d61b535-6164-37e5-a96d-c0a7a6994611',
    '10fd3d86-3461-39f7-843e-d0a0743685a7',
    'Do not step sideways, straight back, use CBM',
    1
),
(
    '7324d5fa-e8f1-390f-927e-077be1618e7f',
    '53dcd13e-0543-394c-94fd-4dd151ff2904',
    'Track foot. Drag LF in with heel. No rondes. Keep feet flat, keep knees flexed. Do not pop up both toes too early. Stay down till lady gets on her RF, then rise.',
    1
),
(
    'e7aa4399-ee54-356a-aded-c68f2163dea7',
    '00435b03-f57c-3d46-a757-df2658da9487',
    'Lower down through the right foot.',
    1
),
(
    'e5c8789b-5da9-3230-924f-582a5187d10c',
    '419ff6f5-f660-373a-90a8-b3af86b0dd53',
    'RF should track under the body.',
    1
),
(
    'f24273fb-1411-357f-8ee3-919cc6ce102a',
    '419ff6f5-f660-373a-90a8-b3af86b0dd53',
    'Body begins turning at the beginning of this step.',
    2
),
(
    '08d8d114-fb67-3cb7-969f-883318ff8bec',
    '419ff6f5-f660-373a-90a8-b3af86b0dd53',
    'Small step. Straight back.',
    3
),
(
    'a64dfbeb-74bc-39ac-ab62-f2a7cf1a2cbd',
    '419ff6f5-f660-373a-90a8-b3af86b0dd53',
    'Keep head weight on your left.',
    4
),
(
    '9e3e043d-da42-3ee8-91af-a550dd96a418',
    '419ff6f5-f660-373a-90a8-b3af86b0dd53',
    'Watch Lady''s position, don''t pivot too much too early, which will peel off from lady.',
    5
),
(
    'e931bb18-fcb0-390d-ac3e-7075aa913d1d',
    '419ff6f5-f660-373a-90a8-b3af86b0dd53',
    'LF fwd in CBMP (small step) RF held in CBMP | DC | TH | up to 1/2 L (Pivot) | ',
    6
),
